   - Update the maximum removal threshold to the maximum of its current value and the new active count plus one.
   - Recalculate the active count as the number of remaining active elements with limits greater than the updated removal threshold using the Fenwick Tree.
4. **Result**: The total sum after processing all possible elements is returned as the maximum achievable sum.

This approach efficiently handles the dynamic constraints of the problem by leveraging sorting and a Fenwick Tree to manage active elements and thresholds optimally. The complexity is O(n log n) due to sorting and logarithmic time operations on the Fenwick Tree.

